cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.PF 

This paper deals with security and networking issues in the Tor system, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the categories of "cs.CR" (Cryptography and Security) and "cs.NI" (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a new method for forming guard sets based on Internet location, which involves constructing a hierarchy, suggesting that it may also belong to the category of "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper uses simulations to evaluate the proposed approach, which suggests that it may belong to the categories of "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks) and "cs.PF" (Performance).
